The paper deals with the matroid secretary problem, which is a problem in algorithmic game theory and falls under the category of combinatorial optimization. The paper presents a new algorithm for this problem, which involves analyzing the competitive ratio of the algorithm. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), followed by cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory), cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
